<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 3:58PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Tazewell, western Bland and northwestern Wythe Counties through 430
PM EDT...
At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Tazewell, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bluefield...
Tazewell...
Ceres...
Burkes Garden...
Gratton...
Tiptop...
and Suiter.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
